<!-- Pain Points -->
<section class="section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">The Problems Our Clients Face</span>
            <h2>Water Challenges That Shut Down Operations and Kill Margins</h2>
            <p>In mining, water problems aren't just operational headaches — they're permit violations, environmental liabilities, and lost recovery that directly hit the bottom line. Here's what we hear every day.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid">
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="wind"></i></div>
                <h3>Dust Permit Violations and PM Exceedances</h3>
                <p>PM10 and PM2.5 exceedances on haul roads trigger regulatory citations, temporary shutdowns, and public complaints — especially near communities. Water trucks can't keep up with 24/7 traffic loads, and they're expensive to operate and maintain.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Automated haul road drip systems apply the right amount of water continuously — without operators, without trucks, and without missed shifts.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="pickaxe"></i></div>
                <h3>Non-Uniform Heap Leach Percolation</h3>
                <p>Uneven solution application across a heap creates channeling, dry zones, and inconsistent recovery rates. Low-recovery areas represent pure profit left in the ground — and you often don't know where they are until it's too late.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Pressure-compensating drip emitters ensure uniform solution distribution across the entire heap — even on significant slopes — maximizing recovery from every ton of ore.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="flask-conical"></i></div>
                <h3>Chemical Exposure Destroying Irrigation Components</h3>
                <p>Standard irrigation components don't survive contact with sulfuric acid, cyanide solutions, and process water. Constant emitter replacement and line failures mean unplanned downtime and escalating maintenance costs.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Our mining-grade driplines and emitters are manufactured from chemical-resistant HDPE and tested specifically for heap leach solution exposure. They last — even in acid environments.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="sprout"></i></div>
                <h3>Reclamation Bonds Requiring Proven Revegetation</h3>
                <p>Mine closure plans require revegetation that regulators can verify. Establishing native plant cover on reclaimed tailings and waste rock — with poor soil and unpredictable rainfall — is one of the hardest parts of closure compliance.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Automated drip irrigation on reclamation sites delivers exactly the moisture needed for native plant establishment — and generates the monitoring data needed for bond release.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="truck"></i></div>
                <h3>Water Truck Costs That Won't Stop Climbing</h3>
                <p>Diesel, driver hours, maintenance, and truck availability make water truck dust suppression one of the most expensive line items in haul road operations. It's also one of the least controllable — when trucks are in maintenance, dust goes unchecked.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Automated drip dust suppression eliminates truck dependence entirely. The system runs on schedule, 24/7, at a fraction of the operating cost — with no drivers required.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="radio"></i></div>
                <h3>No Real-Time Visibility at Remote Sites</h3>
                <p>Mining operations often span miles of remote terrain. A broken line, blocked emitter, or pump failure at a heap leach pad or reclamation site can go unnoticed for days — costing recovery, triggering violations, and escalating repair costs.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ DripSphere OS™ connects to SCADA systems and provides real-time alerts for flow anomalies, pressure drops, and system faults — before small problems become expensive ones.</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

