<!-- Applications -->
<section class="section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Applications</span>
            <h2>Wherever Water Management Matters on Your Site</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="pickaxe"></i></div>
                <h3>Heap Leach Operations</h3>
                <p>Maximize mineral recovery with uniform solution distribution across the full heap. Pressure-compensating emitters maintain equal flow rates at every point — regardless of slope, row length, or pressure variation — so no ore goes under-leached.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="road"></i></div>
                <h3>Haul Road Dust Suppression</h3>
                <p>Automated drip lines along haul road edges apply moisture on schedule and on-demand — eliminating PM exceedances without water trucks. The system runs 24/7 without operators and uses a fraction of the water that trucks waste through evaporation and overlap.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="leaf"></i></div>
                <h3>Mine Reclamation &amp; Revegetation</h3>
                <p>Native plant establishment on reclaimed waste rock, tailings, and pit slopes requires consistent, gentle moisture — not flood or overhead sprinkler cycles. Drip irrigation establishes cover faster and generates the documentation data needed for bond release.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="mountain"></i></div>
                <h3>Tailings Dam Vegetation</h3>
                <p>Stabilizing tailings facilities requires established root systems that prevent erosion and satisfy regulatory inspections. Our systems establish and maintain that cover with minimal water use and zero surface disturbance from equipment access.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="recycle"></i></div>
                <h3>Process Water Reuse</h3>
                <p>Mine process water and treated effluent can replace fresh water sources for dust suppression and revegetation — reducing freshwater withdrawal and turning a disposal problem into a useful resource.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="hard-hat"></i></div>
                <h3>Crusher &amp; Transfer Point Dust</h3>
                <p>Crusher feed, transfer points, and stockpile areas generate point-source dust that's hard to control without fogging or misting. Precision micro-drip systems apply moisture exactly where needed without waterlogging stockpiles or affecting material handling.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

